misc.label: AlertNavigationHandler
description: Returns information that can be used to navigate to a specific page to view the given rule.
returnComment:
A URL that is meant to be relative to your application id, or a state object that your application uses to render
the rule. This information is intended to be used with cores NavigateToApp function, along with the application id that was
originally registered to {@link PluginSetupContract.registerNavigation }.

children.label: rule
description: The rule to view

children.label: registerNavigation
description:
Register a customized view of the particular rule type. Stack Management provides a generic overview, but a developer can register a
custom navigation to provide the user an extra link to a more curated view. The alerting plugin doesn't actually do
anything with this information, but it can be used by other plugins via the `getNavigation` functionality. Currently
the trigger_actions_ui plugin uses it to expose the link from the generic rule details view in Stack Management.

children.label: applicationId
description: The application id that the user should be navigated to, to view a particular rule in a custom way.

children.label: ruleType
description:
The rule type that has been registered with Alerting.Server.PluginSetupContract.registerType. If
no such rule with that id exists, a warning is output to the console log. It used to throw an error, but that was temporarily moved
because it was causing flaky test failures with https://github.com/elastic/kibana/issues/59229 and needs to be
investigated more.

children.label: handler
description:
The navigation handler should return either a relative URL, or a state object. This information can be used,
in conjunction with the consumer id, to navigate the user to a custom URL to view a rule's details.

children.label: registerDefaultNavigation
description:
Register a customized view for all rule types with this application id. Stack Management provides a generic overview, but a developer can register a
custom navigation to provide the user an extra link to a more curated view. The alerting plugin doesn't actually do
anything with this information, but it can be used by other plugins via the `getNavigation` functionality. Currently
the trigger_actions_ui plugin uses it to expose the link from the generic rule details view in Stack Management.

children.label: applicationId
description: The application id that the user should be navigated to, to view a particular rule in a custom way.

children.label: handler
description:
The navigation handler should return either a relative URL, or a state object. This information can be used,
in conjunction with the consumer id, to navigate the user to a custom URL to view a rule's details.

children.label: ruleActionParamsSchema
description:
The schema of the action persisted
in the rule. The schema will be validated
when a rule is created or updated.
The schema should be backwards compatible
and should never introduce any breaking
changes.

children.label: getKibanaPrivileges
signature: ((args: { consumer: string; producer: string; }) => string[]) | undefined

children.label: context
description:
Specifies the target alerts-as-data resource
for this rule type. All alerts created with the same
context are written to the same alerts-as-data index.

All custom mappings defined for a context must be the same!

children.label: mappings
description:
Specifies custom mappings for the target alerts-as-data
index. These mappings will be translated into a component template
and used in the index template for the index.

children.label: shouldWrite
description:
Optional flag to opt into writing alerts as data. When not specified
defaults to false. We need this because we needed all previous rule
registry rules to register with the framework in order to install
Elasticsearch assets but we don't want to migrate them to using
the framework for writing alerts as data until all the pieces are ready

children.label: useEcs
description: Optional flag to include a reference to the ECS component template.

children.label: useLegacyAlerts
description:
Optional flag to include a reference to the legacy alert component template.
Any rule type that is migrating from the rule registry should set this
flag to true to ensure their alerts-as-data indices are backwards compatible.

children.label: isSpaceAware
description:
Optional flag to indicate that resources should be space-aware. When set to
true, alerts-as-data resources will be created for every space where a rule
of this type runs.

children.label: secondaryAlias
description: Optional secondary alias to use. This alias should not include the namespace.

children.label: formatAlert
description: Optional function to format each alert in summarizedAlerts right after fetching them.
